# StudySync Project To-Do List

This document tracks the tasks required to bring StudySync from design to implementation.

## 📋 1. PRD & Requirements
- [ ] **Finalize Data Models**: Define schema for Users, Rooms, Friends, and Messages.
- [ ] **Edge Case Specification**: Document behavior for full rooms, disconnected participants, and failed authentication.
- [ ] **AI Bot Roadmap**: Define the initial "Coming Soon" placeholder requirements and future AI capabilities.
- [ ] **Moderation Policy**: Define Admin rules for kicking/muting and reporting users.
- [ ] **Performance Targets**: Set targets for video latency and page load speeds.

## 🎨 2. Design & UX
- [ ] **UI Component Library**: Create reusable components for buttons (purple gradients), inputs, and cards (12-16px radius).
- [ ] **Hero Section Mockup**: Design the high-impact landing page with parallax and floating elements.
- [ ] **Video Interface Grid**: Design the responsive Discord-style video grid for 2-8 participants.
- [ ] **Dark Mode Implementation Plan**: Define color tokens for seamless switching between white/black backgrounds.
- [ ] **Micro-animations**: Design hover effects for room cards and breadcrumb transitions.
- [ ] **Pomodoro UI**: Design the circular progress indicator and sound notification interaction.

## 💻 3. Tech Stack & Implementation
- [ ] **Project Initialization**: Setup Next.js with TypeScript and a structured folder system.
- [ ] **Authentication Setup**: Integrate NextAuth.js for Google OAuth and JWT session handling.
- [ ] **Real-time Infrastructure**: Implement Socket.io for live room updates and global chat.
- [ ] **Video Implementation**: Research and integrate WebRTC (e.g., SimplePeer or a managed service like Daily.co).
- [ ] **Database Setup**: Configure PostgreSQL with Prisma for efficient data management.
- [ ] **Global State Management**: Setup state for Pomodoro timers and active room status.
- [ ] **Deployment Pipeline**: Configure CI/CD for automated testing and staging deployments.

---

